"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-03-parchment-starts-defence-110m-hurdles-olympic-crown\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France - Defending champion Hansle Parchment will begin his quest for back-to-back titles at the Olympic Games when he competes in the 110m hurdles heats at the Stade De France on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 51, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hansle Parchment\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\"}, {\"begin\": 168, \"end\": 183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade De France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event is scheduled to begin at 4:50 am Jamaica time.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Parchment, who is Jamaica's most decorated sprint hurdler, is to be joined in the event by countrymen and Olympic debutants Rasheed Broadbell and Orlando Bennett.\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0299511290633872e-16, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parchment, a veteran in the sport at age 34, won the gold medal at the Tokyo Olympic Games in 2021 and bronze at the 2012 Games in London.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999766318981, \"rank\": 2.3368263016795203e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, he will enter the Paris Olympic Games as the third fastest Jamaican in the event this year with a season's best time of 13.19 seconds.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Broadbell, the 2022 Commonwealth Games champion, along with Bennett, are the quickest Jamaican athletes over the obstacle event, with their time of 13.18, achieved when both men finished just ahead of Parchment in the final of the event at the National Championships in June.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 787, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.8680751519636599, \"rank\": 0.15197399411531703, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parchment, who has a personal best of 12.93, is ranked the 18th-fastest man over the distance this year.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grant Holloway of the United States is the quickest man globally this year with 12.86.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1083, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grant Holloway\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\"}, {\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9903833667704067, \"rank\": 0.008133296165077913, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am feeling good so far, I am feeling like things are coming together and I am getting fit, and I am definitely looking forward to the start of the Olympics,\\\" said Parchment.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parchment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5122709169232097e-17, \"text\": \"Parchment\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parchment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parchment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have had some time to really settle down [after the Olympic trial] and really focus on my training without any distraction.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like I am a lot higher now than where I was at the trial, and so mentally, I am ready,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Jamaica's reigning world women's 200m champion Shericka Jackson, who recently pulled out of the 100m event, is down to compete in the 200m heats on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0299511290633872e-16, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will be joined in the event by compatriots Nisha Burgher and Lanae-Tava Thomas.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1832, \"enti